00:01:39,599 --> 00:01:40,500
(grunts)

4
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:41,500
- Eat this!

5
00:01:42,802 --> 00:01:44,604
It's not Maya's Fault!

6
00:01:49,042 --> 00:01:51,943
- Come on Mitsuomi, you've
already pushed yourself.

7
00:01:51,944 --> 00:01:53,478
You know as well as I that

8
00:01:53,479 --> 00:01:55,748
this is not the place for
us to settle our score.

9
00:01:57,950 --> 00:02:00,585
In a month from now, the
preliminaries will begin.

10
00:02:00,586 --> 00:02:03,688
We can settle things
then, once and for all.

11
00:02:03,689 --> 00:02:06,359
(intense music)

12
00:02:09,462 --> 00:02:13,799
- [Aya] Let's see. I think
it has to be this way.

13
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:16,334
(Souichiro groans)

14
00:02:16,335 --> 00:02:18,203
- How much farther
do we gotta go?

15
00:02:18,204 --> 00:02:20,272
- We're almost there.

16
00:02:20,273 --> 00:02:21,339
- This blows.

17
00:02:21,340 --> 00:02:22,175
(chime)

18
00:02:22,176 --> 00:02:23,442
- I've made arrangements

19
00:02:23,443 --> 00:02:24,843
for you to receive
special training.

20
00:02:24,844 --> 00:02:26,311
Aya will take you there.

21
00:02:26,312 --> 00:02:27,345
(Aya laughs)

22
00:02:27,346 --> 00:02:29,381
- Special training?

23
00:02:29,382 --> 00:02:30,882
- Listen up,

24
00:02:30,883 --> 00:02:33,018
the real fight to win is the
fight against one's self.

25
00:02:33,019 --> 00:02:34,420
You must never forget that.

26
00:02:36,222 --> 00:02:38,890
(Souichiro grumbles)

27
00:02:38,891 --> 00:02:39,958
- Souichiro sama?

28
00:02:39,959 --> 00:02:41,894
- Huh? Right.

29
00:02:42,895 --> 00:02:44,429
(footsteps)

30
00:02:44,430 --> 00:02:47,032
Why the hell are you so
excited about all this anyway?

31
00:02:47,033 --> 00:02:48,833
- Well of course I'm excited.

32
00:02:48,834 --> 00:02:50,735
We're going on a date after all.

33
00:02:50,736 --> 00:02:52,872
- There's no way you
can call this a date.

34
00:02:54,106 --> 00:02:55,774
- I don't know why I even try.

35
00:02:55,775 --> 00:02:57,909
All you think about
is my sister anyway.

36
00:02:57,910 --> 00:02:58,977
- Huh?

37
00:02:58,978 --> 00:03:01,213
- Oh, nevermind, just forget it.

38
00:03:01,214 --> 00:03:03,448
Now come on, we gotta hurry.

39
00:03:03,449 --> 00:03:04,784
- Yo! Let go!

40
00:03:06,419 --> 00:03:08,921
(bird tweets)

41
00:03:11,557 --> 00:03:13,291
This place?

42
00:03:13,292 --> 00:03:15,962
(calming music)

43
00:03:17,463 --> 00:03:18,897
(Souichiro groans)

44
00:03:18,898 --> 00:03:21,066
- It does seem a
little run-down.

45
00:03:21,067 --> 00:03:23,902
Excuse me? We're
with the Juken Club

46
00:03:23,903 --> 00:03:25,571
from Toudou Academy.

47
00:03:27,573 --> 00:03:30,709
- I have been waiting
for you. Come in.

48
00:03:30,710 --> 00:03:33,079
- That voice. Is that my mom?

49
00:03:34,246 --> 00:03:36,214
What the hell are
you doing here?

50
00:03:36,215 --> 00:03:39,617
- I'm here to give you some
special coaching Souichiro.

51
00:03:39,618 --> 00:03:41,721
It will be me and
one more person.

52
00:03:43,189 --> 00:03:46,491
- [Dogen] The man who
wards off evil, welcome.

53
00:03:46,492 --> 00:03:50,362
- My master and the previous
head of the Takayanagi Clan,

54
00:03:50,363 --> 00:03:52,097
Dogen Takayanagi.

55
00:03:52,098 --> 00:03:54,033
- Is that... Takayanagi?

56
00:03:55,868 --> 00:04:00,706
(door creaks) (footsteps)

57
00:04:02,174 --> 00:04:05,211
- It's finally happened. Your
father has just made his move.

58
00:04:08,714 --> 00:04:09,881
(Souichiro mumbles)

59
00:04:09,882 --> 00:04:11,382
- [Makiko] Close
your mouth Souichiro,

60
00:04:11,383 --> 00:04:13,452
there's no time for you
to be gaping like a fool.

61
00:04:14,620 --> 00:04:16,454
You only have one
month to train.

62
00:04:16,455 --> 00:04:18,590
That said, a well
utilized second

63
00:04:18,591 --> 00:04:21,593
can yield far more
than 10 wasted years.

64
00:04:21,594 --> 00:04:24,362
Memorize those words
and train hard.

65
00:04:24,363 --> 00:04:26,531
- [Aya Internally]
Who is this woman?

66
00:04:26,532 --> 00:04:28,666
I've seen her with my
Dragon's Eye before.

67
00:04:28,667 --> 00:04:30,669
(chime)

68
00:04:31,971 --> 00:04:35,340
This... this is
Souichiro Sama's Mother.

69
00:04:35,341 --> 00:04:37,176
- (sighs) Let's go Aya.

70
00:04:38,010 --> 00:04:39,077
(Aya squeaks)

71
00:04:39,078 --> 00:04:41,846
Screw this, It's freaking lame.

72
00:04:41,847 --> 00:04:43,047
Parents got no place

73
00:04:43,048 --> 00:04:44,917
sticking their nose
into their kid's fights

74
00:04:46,085 --> 00:04:48,119
and besides, it's all
this old man's fault

75
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:50,855
that Natsume's
brother is dead now.

76
00:04:50,856 --> 00:04:53,258
I'm better off just picking
fights on street corners

77
00:04:53,259 --> 00:04:55,326
than trying to learn
anything from that guy.

78
00:04:55,327 --> 00:04:57,997
- Huh? Oh, well, Souichiro Sama.

79
00:05:00,099 --> 00:05:01,099
[Laughs]

80
00:05:04,203 --> 00:05:06,471
- Well, that's a
rational deduction.

81
00:05:06,472 --> 00:05:08,840
If Makiko hadn't
personally asked me this,

82
00:05:08,841 --> 00:05:11,276
there's no way I
would've agreed to it.

83
00:05:11,277 --> 00:05:14,279
However, this also
offers me an opportunity

84
00:05:14,280 --> 00:05:16,281
to clean up a mess
that I created.

85
00:05:16,282 --> 00:05:18,750
Beyond playing with
a child on a mat,

86
00:05:18,751 --> 00:05:21,953
it's true these old bones may
not be able to show you much,

87
00:05:21,954 --> 00:05:23,588
but there's still
more I can teach you

88
00:05:23,589 --> 00:05:24,923
if you're willing to learn.

89
00:05:26,258 --> 00:05:28,860
- Souichiro. You
said it yourself.

90
00:05:28,861 --> 00:05:31,396
One of the crucial paths
to becoming stronger

91
00:05:31,397 --> 00:05:34,466
is to increase the number of
battles that you have been in.

92
00:05:36,235 --> 00:05:38,403
You're missing a
great opportunity.

93
00:05:38,404 --> 00:05:39,937
If you choose to stay here,

94
00:05:39,938 --> 00:05:42,874
you'll find your chances
to fight are plenty.

95
00:05:42,875 --> 00:05:46,077
- Huh? What does
she mean by that?

96
00:05:46,078 --> 00:05:47,346
[Wind Picks Up]

97
00:05:50,816 --> 00:05:51,817
- Forget it.

98
00:05:52,851 --> 00:05:54,253
- Souichiro Sama?

99
00:05:56,889 --> 00:05:58,123
Souichiro Sama?

100
00:06:00,325 --> 00:06:01,993
- [Dogen] Hmm, well so far,

101
00:06:01,994 --> 00:06:05,196
things are going exactly as
you predicted they would.

102
00:06:05,197 --> 00:06:07,231
- Well, he's just
that kind of boy

103
00:06:07,232 --> 00:06:09,033
- Now, phase two.

104
00:06:09,034 --> 00:06:10,802
- Mitsuomi's strength
is already up there

105
00:06:10,803 --> 00:06:12,436
in the realm of the gods.

106
00:06:12,437 --> 00:06:15,406
It's foolish to attack him
in a straightforward manner.

107
00:06:15,407 --> 00:06:16,574
We must wait and see.

108
00:06:16,575 --> 00:06:17,743
[Tile Crunching]

109
00:06:19,311 --> 00:06:20,444
[Air Wooshing]

110
00:06:20,445 --> 00:06:22,346
Will he fly in the skies,

111
00:06:22,347 --> 00:06:24,650
or will he paint the
earth with his blood?

112
00:06:26,318 --> 00:06:30,188
When that door opens, which
one will reveal itself?

113
00:06:30,189 --> 00:06:33,925
A sky dragon, or a black dragon?

114
00:06:33,926 --> 00:06:34,926
[Footsteps]

115
00:06:36,662 --> 00:06:38,729
- [Aya] Are you really
going to go home?

116
00:06:38,730 --> 00:06:41,165
A chance like this
doesn't come everyday.

117
00:06:41,166 --> 00:06:43,535
Master Dogen is really
quite knowledgeable.

118
00:06:44,670 --> 00:06:46,904
- Come on, you're not
getting it are ya?

119
00:06:46,905 --> 00:06:48,573
That old man is
the guy responsible

120
00:06:48,574 --> 00:06:50,541
for killing your brother.

121
00:06:50,542 --> 00:06:51,809
- I know that.

122
00:06:51,810 --> 00:06:53,544
- Hey, I've got a
newsflash for you;

123
00:06:53,545 --> 00:06:56,747
You're more than just a little
wacked out sometimes Aya.

124
00:06:56,748 --> 00:06:58,115
- Well what about you?

125
00:06:58,116 --> 00:07:00,518
You're completely
intolerant of everyone else,

126
00:07:00,519 --> 00:07:01,953
and you're short!

127
00:07:01,954 --> 00:07:04,822
- You call me short again,
and I will kill you.

128
00:07:04,823 --> 00:07:09,260
- You'd kill me? You would
try to kill me Souichiro Sama?

129
00:07:09,261 --> 00:07:10,261
As if you could.

130
00:07:11,663 --> 00:07:12,597
- What did you say?

131
00:07:12,598 --> 00:07:14,032
[Katana Clinking]

132
00:07:16,902 --> 00:07:18,303
[Souichiro Gasps]

133
00:07:21,740 --> 00:07:23,741
- Now if you still
think you can,

134
00:07:23,742 --> 00:07:25,544
go ahead, try and kill me.

135
00:07:27,679 --> 00:07:29,747
You're all talk and no action.

136
00:07:29,748 --> 00:07:32,083
You're no tough guy.
You're just a poser,

137
00:07:32,084 --> 00:07:34,252
and posers are
nothing but losers!

138
00:07:36,855 --> 00:07:38,489
You're the weakest
member of our club

139
00:07:38,490 --> 00:07:40,391
and you don't do
anything about it.

140
00:07:40,392 --> 00:07:42,226
You're never gonna
get any stronger,

141
00:07:42,227 --> 00:07:43,562
not acting like this.

142
00:07:44,930 --> 00:07:47,998
- [Aya Internally] I'm
sorry. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

143
00:07:47,999 --> 00:07:51,102
I'm sorry. But if you work hard,

144
00:07:51,103 --> 00:07:53,537
and do the best
you possibly can,

145
00:07:53,538 --> 00:07:56,774
I know Souichiro Sama that
you'll become stronger

146
00:07:56,775 --> 00:07:58,076
than everyone else.

147
00:07:58,944 --> 00:08:01,580
So for now, please forgive me.

148
00:08:03,682 --> 00:08:06,350
- [Souichiro Internally]
What? I'm the weakest?

149
00:08:06,351 --> 00:08:07,752
I'm the one who doesn't try?

150
00:08:09,821 --> 00:08:13,691
Maybe she's right. I got
myself into this school,

151
00:08:13,692 --> 00:08:15,327
but I got nothing
to show for it.

152
00:08:16,495 --> 00:08:18,729
I've just fought a bunch
of half-assed fights.

153
00:08:18,730 --> 00:08:20,098
How could I be so lame?

154
00:08:21,299 --> 00:08:24,034
I haven't won a single
fight fair and square.

155
00:08:24,035 --> 00:08:27,239
I'm pathetic. I haven't
gotten any tougher at all.

156
00:08:29,174 --> 00:08:32,811
I'm totally blowing my chance
to get stronger, aren't I?

157
00:08:33,979 --> 00:08:36,413
(footsteps)

158
00:08:36,414 --> 00:08:37,414
Hey!

159
00:08:40,085 --> 00:08:42,020
Aya, you're absolutely right.

160
00:08:43,188 --> 00:08:45,389
Everything you just
said is totally true.

161
00:08:45,390 --> 00:08:47,091
Let's go back.

162
00:08:47,092 --> 00:08:48,692
- So...

163
00:08:48,693 --> 00:08:49,927
Souichiro Sama.

164
00:08:49,928 --> 00:08:51,695
- Hey! What are you
doing? Get off me!

165
00:08:51,696 --> 00:08:54,398
(grass rustles)

166
00:08:54,399 --> 00:08:57,401
(tense orchestral music)

167
00:08:57,402 --> 00:08:59,504
(grunts)

168
00:09:03,842 --> 00:09:05,142
(blade spinning)

169
00:09:05,143 --> 00:09:06,644
- What the hell?

170
00:09:06,645 --> 00:09:07,811
- You know, your mother
said something back there

171
00:09:07,812 --> 00:09:09,480
that I can't get out of my head.

172
00:09:09,481 --> 00:09:10,481
- What?

173
00:09:11,249 --> 00:09:12,750
- If you choose to stay here,

174
00:09:12,751 --> 00:09:15,486
you'll find your chances
to fight are plenty.

175
00:09:15,487 --> 00:09:16,653
- So what does that mean?

176
00:09:16,654 --> 00:09:18,589
- Well, it's about Master Dogen.

177
00:09:18,590 --> 00:09:19,957
He may not be in charge anymore,

178
00:09:19,958 --> 00:09:21,392
but he still has
a lot of influence

179
00:09:21,393 --> 00:09:22,860
in the martial arts world.

180
00:09:22,861 --> 00:09:25,462
When Mitsuomi pushed
out Master Dogen,

181
00:09:25,463 --> 00:09:29,366
he forced the leaders of the
old 12 clans to retire as well.

182
00:09:29,367 --> 00:09:31,268
The fact that the
12 divine lords

183
00:09:31,269 --> 00:09:33,404
of the Flying Phoenix
are still out there

184
00:09:33,405 --> 00:09:35,973
has got to pose a threat
to the current regime.

185
00:09:35,974 --> 00:09:38,475
That's gotta be what your
mother was trying to tel you.

186
00:09:38,476 --> 00:09:40,310
That if Master
Dogen made a move,

187
00:09:40,311 --> 00:09:43,347
it wouldn't be long before
Mitsuomi sent his henchmen over.

188
00:09:43,348 --> 00:09:46,250
- Well, then the most
dangerous place to be right now

189
00:09:46,251 --> 00:09:48,519
is in that house
with the old man.

190
00:09:48,520 --> 00:09:50,788
We don't have time to deal
with these boy scouts.

191
00:09:50,789 --> 00:09:52,556
Bust 'em through the
center. Let's go!

192
00:09:52,557 --> 00:09:53,657
- Right!

193
00:09:53,658 --> 00:09:55,759
(Running)

194
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:57,762
(Groan)

195
00:09:59,998 --> 00:10:03,001
(Students mumbling)

196
00:10:04,769 --> 00:10:06,303
- [Girl] Come on,
you're slow foreign boy.

197
00:10:06,304 --> 00:10:07,704
I bet there's turtles out there

198
00:10:07,705 --> 00:10:09,640
who know how to run
better than you.

199
00:10:09,641 --> 00:10:11,742
(intense groaning)

200
00:10:11,743 --> 00:10:13,076
That's it. There's
no point to this

201
00:10:13,077 --> 00:10:14,979
if you don't get
your brain around it.

202
00:10:16,181 --> 00:10:17,915
Think about how you're
using your shoulders,

203
00:10:17,916 --> 00:10:21,318
and don't lose that
tension in your abdomen.

204
00:10:21,319 --> 00:10:22,253
- [Boy Interally]
Souichiro scores

205
00:10:22,254 --> 00:10:23,487
and gets special training,

206
00:10:23,488 --> 00:10:26,657
and I gotta do wind
sprints all damn day.

207
00:10:26,658 --> 00:10:28,191
- You don't need to worry.

208
00:10:28,192 --> 00:10:30,160
Takayanagi and I will teach
you some new skills as well

209
00:10:30,161 --> 00:10:32,229
when this is accomplished.

210
00:10:32,230 --> 00:10:33,730
You're quite different
from that boy.

211
00:10:33,731 --> 00:10:35,198
You have an excellent physique

212
00:10:35,199 --> 00:10:37,067
and you know how
to use your brain.

213
00:10:37,068 --> 00:10:38,602
Once you get the hang of things,

214
00:10:38,603 --> 00:10:40,504
you'll quickly become one
of the top ranking students

215
00:10:40,505 --> 00:10:42,005
in the school.

216
00:10:42,006 --> 00:10:43,408
Now pick up the pace!

217
00:10:45,810 --> 00:10:48,979
When it comes to that boy,
it's skill he needs to learn,

218
00:10:48,980 --> 00:10:51,615
and since I don't possess
supernatural powers,

219
00:10:51,616 --> 00:10:53,150
there's no way that
I can teach him

220
00:10:53,151 --> 00:10:54,218
what he needs to know.

221
00:10:55,353 --> 00:10:57,354
(Boy yells)

222
00:10:57,355 --> 00:10:59,256
I wish I could.

223
00:10:59,257 --> 00:11:01,326
(running)

224
00:11:04,195 --> 00:11:06,698
(tense music)

225
00:11:08,833 --> 00:11:10,367
